.SH NAME
Net::Nostr::Wiki \- NIP\-54 Wiki
.SH SYNOPSIS
.IX Header "SYNOPSIS"
.Vb 1
\&    use Net::Nostr::Wiki;
\&
\&    # Wiki article (kind 30818)
\&    my $event = Net::Nostr::Wiki\->article(
\&        pubkey     => $hex_pubkey,
\&        identifier => \*(AqWiki Article\*(Aq,
\&        title      => \*(AqWiki Article\*(Aq,
\&        content    => \*(AqA wiki is a hypertext publication.\*(Aq,
\&    );
\&
\&    # Merge request (kind 818)
\&    my $event = Net::Nostr::Wiki\->merge_request(
\&        pubkey       => $hex_pubkey,
\&        target       => "30818:$dest_pk:bitcoin",
\&        target_relay => \*(Aqwss://relay.com\*(Aq,
\&        source       => $source_event_id,
\&        source_relay => \*(Aqwss://relay.com\*(Aq,
\&        destination  => $dest_pk,
\&        content      => \*(AqAdded block size info\*(Aq,
\&    );
\&
\&    # Wiki redirect (kind 30819)
\&    my $event = Net::Nostr::Wiki\->redirect(
\&        pubkey       => $hex_pubkey,
\&        identifier   => \*(Aqbtc\*(Aq,
\&        target       => "30818:$pk:bitcoin",
\&        target_relay => \*(Aqwss://relay.com\*(Aq,
\&    );
\&
\&    # Normalize a d tag
\&    my $dtag = Net::Nostr::Wiki\->normalize_dtag(\*(AqWiki Article\*(Aq);
\&    # "wiki\-article"
\&
\&    # Parse any wiki event
\&    my $parsed = Net::Nostr::Wiki\->from_event($event);
\&
\&    # Validate
\&    Net::Nostr::Wiki\->validate($event);
\&
\&    # Resolve wikilinks in Djot content
\&    my $resolved = Net::Nostr::Wiki\->resolve_wikilinks(\*(Aq[cryptocurrency][]\*(Aq);
.Ve
.SH DESCRIPTION
.IX Header "DESCRIPTION"
Implements NIP\-54 (Wiki). Three event kinds are used:
.IP \(bu 4
\&\fBWiki Article\fR (kind 30818) \- An addressable event for
encyclopedia entries. Articles are identified by lowercase, normalized
\&\f(CW\*(C`d\*(C'\fR tags. Content should be Djot with NIP\-21 links and wikilinks.
Multiple people may write articles about the same subject.
.IP \(bu 4
\&\fBMerge Request\fR (kind 818) \- A regular event requesting a
merge from a forked article into the source. Directed to a pubkey,
references the original article and the modified version. The
destination pubkey can accept or reject via NIP\-25 reactions.
.IP \(bu 4
\&\fBWiki Redirect\fR (kind 30819) \- An addressable event that
redirects one article name to another. Useful for disambiguation
and alternative names.
.PP
Articles support fork and defer markers on \f(CW\*(C`a\*(C'\fR and \f(CW\*(C`e\*(C'\fR tags.
Fork markers indicate the article was derived from another version.
Defer markers indicate the author considers another entry as a better
version of their own.
.SH CONSTANTS
.IX Header "CONSTANTS"
.SS WIKI_RELAY_LIST_KIND
.IX Subsection "WIKI_RELAY_LIST_KIND"
.Vb 2
\&    use Net::Nostr::Wiki;
\&    my $kind = Net::Nostr::Wiki::WIKI_RELAY_LIST_KIND;  # 10102
.Ve
.PP
NIP\-51 list kind for wiki\-specific relay lists. Clients can create
kind 10102 lists to indicate preferred relays for wiki content.
.SH CONSTRUCTOR
.IX Header "CONSTRUCTOR"
.SS new
.IX Subsection "new"
.Vb 4
\&    my $w = Net::Nostr::Wiki\->new(
\&        identifier => \*(Aqbitcoin\*(Aq,
\&        title      => \*(AqBitcoin\*(Aq,
\&    );
.Ve
.PP
Creates a new \f(CW\*(C`Net::Nostr::Wiki\*(C'\fR object. Croaks on unknown arguments.
.SH "CLASS METHODS"
.IX Header "CLASS METHODS"
.SS article
.IX Subsection "article"
.Vb 11
\&    my $event = Net::Nostr::Wiki\->article(
\&        pubkey     => $hex_pubkey,       # required
\&        identifier => $name,             # required (d tag, auto\-normalized)
\&        content    => $djot_content,     # required
\&        title      => $display_title,    # optional
\&        summary    => $description,      # optional
\&        fork_a     => [$coord, $relay],  # optional (a tag with fork marker)
\&        fork_e     => [$id, $relay],     # optional (e tag with fork marker)
\&        defer_a    => [$coord, $relay],  # optional (a tag with defer marker)
\&        defer_e    => [$id, $relay],     # optional (e tag with defer marker)
\&    );
.Ve
.PP
Creates a kind 30818 wiki article Net::Nostr::Event. The \f(CW\*(C`identifier\*(C'\fR
is automatically normalized per the NIP\-54 d tag normalization rules.
.SS merge_request
.IX Subsection "merge_request"
.Vb 11
\&    my $event = Net::Nostr::Wiki\->merge_request(
\&        pubkey       => $hex_pubkey,       # required
\&        target       => $article_coord,    # required (a tag)
\&        target_relay => $relay_url,        # optional
\&        source       => $event_id,         # required (e tag with source marker)
\&        source_relay => $relay_url,        # optional
\&        destination  => $dest_pubkey,      # required (p tag)
\&        base_version => $event_id,         # optional (e tag, version base)
\&        base_relay   => $relay_url,        # optional
\&        content      => $explanation,      # optional, defaults to \*(Aq\*(Aq
\&    );
.Ve
.PP
Creates a kind 818 merge request Net::Nostr::Event. The \f(CW\*(C`source\*(C'\fR
event ID MUST be of a kind 30818 event.
.SS redirect
.IX Subsection "redirect"
.Vb 6
\&    my $event = Net::Nostr::Wiki\->redirect(
\&        pubkey       => $hex_pubkey,       # required
\&        identifier   => $source_name,      # required (d tag, auto\-normalized)
\&        target       => $article_coord,    # required (a tag)
\&        target_relay => $relay_url,        # optional
\&    );
.Ve
.PP
Creates a kind 30819 wiki redirect Net::Nostr::Event. The \f(CW\*(C`identifier\*(C'\fR
is automatically normalized. Content is always empty.
.SS normalize_dtag
.IX Subsection "normalize_dtag"
.Vb 2
\&    my $normalized = Net::Nostr::Wiki\->normalize_dtag(\*(AqWiki Article\*(Aq);
\&    # "wiki\-article"
.Ve
.PP
Normalizes a string per NIP\-54 rules:
.IP \(bu 4
Lowercase all letters
.IP \(bu 4
Whitespace converted to \f(CW\*(C`\-\*(C'\fR
.IP \(bu 4
Punctuation and symbols removed
.IP \(bu 4
Consecutive \f(CW\*(C`\-\*(C'\fR collapsed
.IP \(bu 4
Leading/trailing \f(CW\*(C`\-\*(C'\fR removed
.IP \(bu 4
Non\-ASCII letters preserved as UTF\-8
.IP \(bu 4
Numbers preserved
.SS from_event
.IX Subsection "from_event"
.Vb 1
\&    my $w = Net::Nostr::Wiki\->from_event($event);
.Ve
.PP
Parses a kind 30818, 818, or 30819 event into a \f(CW\*(C`Net::Nostr::Wiki\*(C'\fR
object. Returns \f(CW\*(C`undef\*(C'\fR for unrecognized kinds.
.SS validate
.IX Subsection "validate"
.Vb 1
\&    Net::Nostr::Wiki\->validate($event);
.Ve
.PP
Validates a NIP\-54 event. Croaks if:
.IP \(bu 4
Kind is not 30818, 818, or 30819
.IP \(bu 4
Kind 30818 missing \f(CW\*(C`d\*(C'\fR tag
.IP \(bu 4
Kind 818 missing \f(CW\*(C`a\*(C'\fR, \f(CW\*(C`p\*(C'\fR, or \f(CW\*(C`e\*(C'\fR tag with \f(CW\*(C`source\*(C'\fR marker
.IP \(bu 4
Kind 30819 missing \f(CW\*(C`d\*(C'\fR or \f(CW\*(C`a\*(C'\fR tag
.PP
Returns 1 on success.
.SS resolve_wikilinks
.IX Subsection "resolve_wikilinks"
.Vb 1
\&    my $resolved = Net::Nostr::Wiki\->resolve_wikilinks($djot_content);
.Ve
.PP
Resolves reference\-style links in Djot content to wiki article links.
Links with defined references (\f(CW\*(C`[label]: target\*(C'\fR at end of content)
are preserved. Undefined reference\-style links become wikilinks using
\&\f(CW\*(C`nostr:30818:normalized\-name\*(C'\fR URIs.
.PP
Handles both implicit (\f(CW\*(C`[text][]\*(C'\fR) and explicit (\f(CW\*(C`[text][Label]\*(C'\fR)
reference\-style links.
.SH ACCESSORS
.IX Header "ACCESSORS"
.SS identifier
.IX Subsection "identifier"
The normalized \f(CW\*(C`d\*(C'\fR tag value (kinds 30818, 30819).
.SS title
.IX Subsection "title"
Display title from \f(CW\*(C`title\*(C'\fR tag (kind 30818).
.SS summary
.IX Subsection "summary"
Description from \f(CW\*(C`summary\*(C'\fR tag (kind 30818).
.SS fork_a
.IX Subsection "fork_a"
Arrayref \f(CW\*(C`[$coord, $relay]\*(C'\fR from \f(CW\*(C`a\*(C'\fR tag with \f(CW\*(C`fork\*(C'\fR marker.
.SS fork_e
.IX Subsection "fork_e"
Arrayref \f(CW\*(C`[$id, $relay]\*(C'\fR from \f(CW\*(C`e\*(C'\fR tag with \f(CW\*(C`fork\*(C'\fR marker.
.SS defer_a
.IX Subsection "defer_a"
Arrayref \f(CW\*(C`[$coord, $relay]\*(C'\fR from \f(CW\*(C`a\*(C'\fR tag with \f(CW\*(C`defer\*(C'\fR marker.
.SS defer_e
.IX Subsection "defer_e"
Arrayref \f(CW\*(C`[$id, $relay]\*(C'\fR from \f(CW\*(C`e\*(C'\fR tag with \f(CW\*(C`defer\*(C'\fR marker.
.SS target
.IX Subsection "target"
The article coordinate from \f(CW\*(C`a\*(C'\fR tag (kinds 818, 30819).
.SS target_relay
.IX Subsection "target_relay"
Relay hint from \f(CW\*(C`a\*(C'\fR tag (kinds 818, 30819).
.SS destination
.IX Subsection "destination"
Destination pubkey from \f(CW\*(C`p\*(C'\fR tag (kind 818).
.SS source
.IX Subsection "source"
Source event ID from \f(CW\*(C`e\*(C'\fR tag with \f(CW\*(C`source\*(C'\fR marker (kind 818).
.SS source_relay
.IX Subsection "source_relay"
Relay from \f(CW\*(C`e\*(C'\fR tag with \f(CW\*(C`source\*(C'\fR marker (kind 818).
.SS base_version
.IX Subsection "base_version"
Base version event ID from \f(CW\*(C`e\*(C'\fR tag without marker (kind 818).
.SS base_relay
.IX Subsection "base_relay"
Relay from base version \f(CW\*(C`e\*(C'\fR tag (kind 818).
